WEBVTT

00:01.043 --> 00:04.171
(ROCK MUSIC)

00:24.150 --> 00:27.278
MAN: <i>All I've really ever wanted
was adventure.</i>

00:28.529 --> 00:30.656
<i>That's what got me into
the armoured car business.</i>

00:30.823 --> 00:32.241
<i>Between the guns and the cash</i>

00:32.408 --> 00:33.826
<i>and the constant threat
of violence,</i>

00:33.993 --> 00:36.454
<i>it seemed like a total dream.</i>

00:36.620 --> 00:38.080
(MAN SHOUTS INDISTINCTLY)

00:38.247 --> 00:41.584
<i>But that's all it was -
just a dream.</i>

00:43.210 --> 00:45.296
<i>'Cause in reality,
my day-to-day was as boring</i>

00:45.463 --> 00:48.299
<i>as any garbage man, pizza guy
or paperboy.</i>

00:50.301 --> 00:53.012
<i>Pick it up, drop it off,
repeat.</i>

00:53.179 --> 00:55.723
<i>Pick it up,
drop it off, repeat.</i>

00:55.890 --> 00:58.601
<i>Pick it up, drop it off,
repeat.</i>

01:00.603 --> 01:02.438
<i>I used to fantasise
about getting robbed</i>

01:02.605 --> 01:04.190
<i>in the line of duty</i>

01:04.355 --> 01:07.151
<i>just to prove to myself that I would
man up, given the chance.</i>

01:07.318 --> 01:10.529
<i>But I was denied
even that simple pleasure.</i>

01:12.990 --> 01:15.701
<i>I blame popular culture.</i>

01:15.868 --> 01:18.079
<i>See, I grew up
watching spy movies.</i>

01:18.245 --> 01:19.955
<i>They made it seem so fun,</i>

01:20.122 --> 01:22.750
<i>judo-chopping the bad guys
and saving the girl.</i>

01:22.917 --> 01:27.213
<i>I wanted that life,
but it didn't quite pan out that way.</i>

01:27.379 --> 01:29.090
<i>So I settled.</i>

01:29.256 --> 01:32.176
<i>That's about the worst thing you can do,
if I'm honest.</i>

01:32.343 --> 01:34.345
<i>I mean,
until you take a chance in life,</i>

01:34.512 --> 01:36.931
<i>you really never find out
who you are.</i>

01:37.973 --> 01:39.850
<i>My name is David Ghantt.</i>

01:40.017 --> 01:41.644
<i>In 1997,</i>

01:41.811 --> 01:44.688
<i>I was a quiet middle-aged man
knocking on 40.</i>

01:44.855 --> 01:49.902
<i>But then, then the wind blew in
Miss Kelly Campbell.</i>

01:50.069 --> 01:52.279
(ROCK MUSIC CONTINUES)

01:52.446 --> 01:54.281
<i>After four decades of waiting,</i>

01:54.448 --> 01:56.367
<i>my adventure
finally came knocking.</i>

02:01.539 --> 02:05.459
What do you say
you and me rob Loomis Fargo?

02:05.626 --> 02:07.378
- (BLOWS RASPBERRY)
- What? Come on!

02:07.545 --> 02:09.088
That guy just did it
a month ago.

02:09.255 --> 02:10.881
The bank guard? Jacksonville?

02:11.048 --> 02:12.842
- Phillip Johnson.
- Yeah, Phillip Johnson.

02:13.008 --> 02:15.636
Behind this wall,
there is a million dollars.

02:15.803 --> 02:17.555
Give me one reason
why we shouldn't.

02:17.721 --> 02:19.849
Well, for one thing,
we could get fired.

02:20.015 --> 02:21.934
Right?

02:25.813 --> 02:27.398
- Whoo!
- Hot dog!

02:27.565 --> 02:29.358
Not bad.

02:29.525 --> 02:31.235
You know what I'd do
with $1 million?

02:31.402 --> 02:34.572
Buy a crapload of CDs.
Music is very important in my life.

02:34.738 --> 02:36.532
What would you do
with $1 million?

02:36.699 --> 02:39.618
Probably start my own business,
you know?

02:39.785 --> 02:42.538
Maybe go after some felons or convicts,
you know?

02:42.705 --> 02:46.250
Be a bounty hunter or skip tracer
or something like that.

02:54.508 --> 02:56.051
You know, put a cap in there.

02:56.218 --> 02:58.179
- (GUN FIRES)
- (CRIES OUT)

02:58.345 --> 03:00.472
- Oh! Oh! David!
- Oh, that burns!

03:00.639 --> 03:02.224
- Oh, my gosh! Let me see!
- Ow, Kelly!

03:02.391 --> 03:04.310
- Let me see! Let me see!
- Ow! Get it out!

03:04.476 --> 03:05.978
- OK.
- Oh, God, Kelly!

03:06.145 --> 03:07.771
- You're good. You're alright.
- OK.

03:07.938 --> 03:10.107
You're OK. But, man, you nearly
shot yourself a new butthole.

03:10.274 --> 03:12.067
Yeah, went straight down
the crack.

03:12.234 --> 03:14.862
It feels like it just grazed my biscuits
right betwixt them.

03:15.029 --> 03:17.448
- Yeah, doesn't hurt that bad.
- No, I think you're OK.

03:17.615 --> 03:19.825
I mean, you got a nice big hole
in your shorts.

03:19.992 --> 03:21.785
It's just a skin burn.
You're alright.

03:21.952 --> 03:23.454
Yeah.

03:23.621 --> 03:26.040
You go home and you fill your tub
full of whole milk.

03:26.207 --> 03:29.126
- What's...what's that?
- Fill your tub with whole milk.

03:29.293 --> 03:30.544
- Whole milk?
- Yeah.

03:30.711 --> 03:32.671
'Cause the fats, it's the fats
that moisturise the skin.

03:32.838 --> 03:35.090
I got ranch dressing.
I could put a little ranch in.

03:35.257 --> 03:37.676
- (PAGER BUZZES)
- Oh! I'll get it.

03:37.843 --> 03:41.805
Well, if it isn't the future
Mrs David Ghantt calling her honey.

03:41.972 --> 03:44.683
Oh, no, no. That's Jandice.
I'm late.

03:44.850 --> 03:46.644
- I forgot, gosh!
- What? Where you going?

03:46.810 --> 03:48.729
(SIGHS) Engagement photos.

03:48.896 --> 03:50.606
- Oh. That's nice.
- Yeah, so... Yeah!

03:50.773 --> 03:52.441
I'm gonna walk backwards -

03:52.608 --> 03:54.276
I don't want you looking
at my derriere.

03:54.443 --> 03:56.862
Well, I've seen it,
hate to tell ya, crack and all.

03:57.029 --> 03:59.949
Maybe I can stare at your crack
one day and we can get even.

04:02.785 --> 04:04.161
(ROCK MUSIC)

04:04.328 --> 04:05.871
MAN: Hey, Dave!

04:14.964 --> 04:18.259
- MAN: Have another drink.
- (WOMAN ARGUES)

04:18.425 --> 04:20.552
Jandice, I'm sorry I'm late.

04:20.719 --> 04:23.889
That's OK. I'm glad
you got here when you did.

04:24.056 --> 04:27.059
- I've been crying for hours.
- Have you?

04:27.226 --> 04:28.852
Had to put my make-up on

04:29.019 --> 04:30.646
three separate times
'cause of the tears.

04:30.813 --> 04:34.024
Well, third time's a charm.
You look...you look fantastic.

04:34.191 --> 04:36.902
Let's take some pictures.

04:37.069 --> 04:40.030
('ONLY TIME' BY ENYA)

04:45.953 --> 04:51.333
♪ Who can say
where the road goes

04:51.500 --> 04:53.794
♪ Where the day flows

04:53.961 --> 04:57.464
♪ Only time

04:57.631 --> 05:02.261
♪ And who can say
if your love grows

05:02.428 --> 05:05.097
♪ As your heart chose

05:05.264 --> 05:08.517
♪ Only time... ♪

05:09.560 --> 05:11.020
(LOUD FART)

05:11.186 --> 05:12.604
Good lord, Jandice!

05:12.771 --> 05:14.648
JANDICE: I've been saving that
for you.

05:14.815 --> 05:16.692
You farted
right into my butthole.

05:16.859 --> 05:19.069
It's like a fart transplant.

05:19.236 --> 05:21.739
- (INSECT BUZZES)
- So how'd y'all meet?

05:21.905 --> 05:23.782
I'm a sucker
for courtship stories.

05:23.949 --> 05:28.579
Well, if you must know,
a couple years back

05:28.746 --> 05:32.458
I was at a Youth Praise concert
at church,

05:32.624 --> 05:35.127
and I saw the most handsome man

05:35.294 --> 05:37.046
that I had ever seen
in the world.

05:37.212 --> 05:39.506
He was looking right at me.

05:39.673 --> 05:42.343
We went on a date,
and then we fell

05:42.509 --> 05:46.472
very, very, very, very, very,
very, very, very deeply in love.

05:47.723 --> 05:51.018
And then he died. Snakebite.

05:51.185 --> 05:54.021
At his funeral,
I was very, very distraught.

05:54.188 --> 05:56.398
I couldn't keep myself together.

05:56.565 --> 05:59.693
And I saw this...other man,

05:59.860 --> 06:02.196
a distant cousin
of the deceased.

06:02.363 --> 06:05.407
He was a pallbearer
and he was kinda struggling

06:05.574 --> 06:08.494
to hold up
his end of the casket.

06:08.660 --> 06:10.371
I had a hard time lifting it up.

06:10.537 --> 06:12.790
JANDICE: In any case,
we got to talking afterwards.

06:12.956 --> 06:16.293
And I thought,
"Well, that one's dead.

06:16.460 --> 06:18.796
"This one's alive.

06:18.962 --> 06:21.423
"I'll take the live one."

06:23.217 --> 06:25.636
Now here we are,
two years later.

06:27.137 --> 06:29.973
That's, uh, quite a story.

06:30.140 --> 06:32.101
Yeah, we're happy
as all get out.

06:32.267 --> 06:34.895
- I couldn't be happier.
- Me either.

06:37.189 --> 06:39.858
DAVID: <i>Then one day,
things took a turn.</i>

06:40.025 --> 06:42.736
<i>I guess I...I sensed it coming.</i>

06:42.903 --> 06:44.655
<i>But restless souls like Kelly</i>

06:44.822 --> 06:46.949
<i>usually don't stick around
at a place like Loomis.</i>

06:47.116 --> 06:50.327
Here's a little snackaroo.

06:51.412 --> 06:53.497
Taco salad with extra ranch.

06:53.664 --> 06:56.041
- David, thank you.
- Eat up.

06:56.208 --> 06:58.961
I'm not really that hungry.
Not now. I'm sorry.

06:59.128 --> 07:02.423
What's going on now?
Come on, you're just moping around.

07:02.589 --> 07:05.759
Well...Rodney and I broke up.

07:05.926 --> 07:08.762
- No kidding!
- Yep. Last night.

07:08.929 --> 07:10.597
Hey, hey, hey.
What's going on in here?

07:10.764 --> 07:12.975
You all are way behind schedule,
so, Ghantt,

07:13.142 --> 07:15.936
I need you to get your bearded
lady-face out there right now.

07:16.103 --> 07:17.813
Wait, whoa, whoa!
What'd you say to him?

07:17.980 --> 07:19.606
You can't talk to David Ghantt
like that.

07:19.773 --> 07:21.817
He's the only one around here
with half a brain.

07:21.984 --> 07:23.610
He's smarter
than you'll ever be.

07:23.777 --> 07:25.487
- We're gonna be outside, boss.
- No, no, no.

07:25.654 --> 07:27.239
What the hell is your problem
today, Kelly?

07:27.406 --> 07:28.866
Maybe I'm feeling
a little emotional.

07:29.032 --> 07:31.952
Maybe I'm having a bad day, huh?
Does that fit in your schedule?

07:32.119 --> 07:34.455
You know, what I care about is
getting that truck out there,

07:34.621 --> 07:36.331
southbound, A-S-A-effing-P.

07:36.498 --> 07:38.041
And if I don't?

07:38.208 --> 07:39.751
You're fired.

07:39.918 --> 07:41.753
OK, then, fine.

07:41.920 --> 07:43.630
- Fire me, Ashley. Fire me.
- OK.

07:43.797 --> 07:45.424
- Kelly, I don't know...
- No, you know what?

07:45.591 --> 07:48.010
I have been fixing to quit this job
for a long time.

07:48.177 --> 07:50.387
And besides, if I get fired,
I get unemployment.

07:50.554 --> 07:52.681
- That's a good point.
- ASHLEY: Then guess what.

07:52.848 --> 07:54.516
- You're not fired.
- KELLY: OK!

07:54.683 --> 07:56.602
What if I sexually harass
one of your employees, huh?

07:56.768 --> 07:58.812
Then you'll get in trouble
if you don't fire me.

07:58.979 --> 08:01.023
Just walk up to somebody
and go like that.

08:01.190 --> 08:03.066
What if I just do
this kind of thing?

08:03.233 --> 08:05.486
Oh, my gosh, this is so illegal.

08:05.652 --> 08:07.321
You're gonna get fired
for not firing me

08:07.488 --> 08:10.407
because I'm doing something
so sexual and inappropriate...

08:10.574 --> 08:12.409
- Don't.
- ..for the workplace.

08:12.576 --> 08:14.578
- Look at that! Kelly!
- What if I did this?

08:14.745 --> 08:16.788
- Sexual, sexual dancing!
- (DAVID LAUGHS)

08:16.955 --> 08:18.499
(GUNSHOT)

08:21.251 --> 08:23.212
ASHLEY: OK, you're fired now.

08:24.254 --> 08:26.590
Leave the uniform!

08:32.513 --> 08:34.306
Kelly, hold on a second.

08:34.472 --> 08:36.058
I'll clean that up. Just...

08:36.225 --> 08:38.769
(INDISTINCT P.A. ANNOUNCEMENT)

08:38.936 --> 08:42.147
DAVID: Hey, uh... Hey, Kelly?

08:42.313 --> 08:46.276
Can I get your phone number,
you know, just to have it?

08:46.443 --> 08:48.570
Um... Oh, yeah. Sure.

08:50.572 --> 08:52.449
I don't have a pen on me.
(LAUGHS)

08:52.616 --> 08:54.868
No, you don't have no pen.

08:55.035 --> 08:57.913
You got barely anything on
your upper half. You got a bra.

08:58.080 --> 09:00.123
They look good.

09:00.290 --> 09:04.002
I mean, the bra looks nice
and what it encases. Um...

09:04.169 --> 09:06.797
I got a pencil right here.

09:06.964 --> 09:08.674
Great.

09:09.883 --> 09:11.927
- You can just do it on my arm.
- With pencil?

09:12.094 --> 09:13.303
Yeah.

09:14.346 --> 09:15.556
(DAVID GASPS)

09:15.722 --> 09:18.600
Ooh, man, you really gotta
press into the skin

09:18.767 --> 09:20.686
to make this show up.

09:20.852 --> 09:22.646
(INHALES SHARPLY AND GROANS)
Mm-hm.

09:22.813 --> 09:25.482
- Yeah.
- Here you go.

09:25.649 --> 09:28.652
- There's 10 numbers there.
- Oh, yeah.

09:28.819 --> 09:30.529
The 1-4-3 at the end,

09:30.696 --> 09:32.990
that's sort of my thing
I just always do.

09:33.156 --> 09:35.534
It's code for "I love you" -
you know, 'I' is one letter,

09:35.701 --> 09:37.869
'love' is four letters,
'you', three letters.

09:38.036 --> 09:39.871
I've just always done it.
I don't know.

09:40.038 --> 09:41.540
That's my thing.

09:41.707 --> 09:43.333
That's pretty bad-ass.

09:43.500 --> 09:45.168
(LAUGHS) That's cool.

09:45.335 --> 09:47.421
Well, see ya.

09:49.006 --> 09:50.799
OK.

09:50.966 --> 09:55.429
DAVID: <i>Kelly always made me
feel special.</i>

09:55.596 --> 09:57.848
<i>- Like I could do anything.</i>
- (MAN SHOUTS) Idiot!

09:58.015 --> 09:59.808
<i>You know, be anyone.</i>

09:59.975 --> 10:01.810
<i>Watching her leave Loomis
was like</i>

10:01.977 --> 10:04.521
<i>watching a space shuttle
shed its rocket boosters.</i>

10:04.688 --> 10:07.357
<i>The shuttle goes up
to new and exciting places.</i>

10:07.524 --> 10:09.484
<i>Rocket boosters just
burn into the atmosphere</i>

10:09.651 --> 10:11.653
<i>or sink into the ocean.</i>

10:11.820 --> 10:15.073
<i>No-one gives a crap
about rocket boosters.</i>

10:15.240 --> 10:17.701
<i>Now, without
my positive influence,</i>

10:17.868 --> 10:19.703
<i>Kelly fell in with a bad crowd.</i>

10:19.870 --> 10:21.580
<i>In the weeks after she quit,</i>

10:21.747 --> 10:24.374
<i>she was spending all of her time
on the rough side of town</i>

10:24.541 --> 10:27.544
<i>in a double-wide high-rise
belonging to this man,</i>

10:27.711 --> 10:30.756
<i>Steven Eugene Chambers.</i>

10:30.922 --> 10:32.507
<i>I think he was
Kelly's neighbour</i>

10:32.674 --> 10:34.593
<i>or a friend from high school -
might have been both.</i>

10:34.760 --> 10:36.720
<i>Calling Steve
a snake in the grass</i>

10:36.887 --> 10:39.473
<i>is an insult to snakes
and to grass.</i>

10:39.640 --> 10:41.767
<i>He was a petty thief
mostly known for</i>

10:41.933 --> 10:44.978
<i>stealing tiny wheelchairs
from paediatric hospitals.</i>

10:45.145 --> 10:47.439
<i>As for Kelly,
she'd all but forgotten</i>

10:47.606 --> 10:50.651
<i>about her days at Loomis Fargo,
till the company made the news.</i>

10:50.817 --> 10:52.402
NEWSREADER: <i>Police are reporting
that Phillip Johnson,</i>

10:52.569 --> 10:54.613
<i>a Loomis Fargo security guard</i>

10:54.780 --> 10:58.950
<i>accused of stealing $20 million,
has been arrested.</i>

10:59.117 --> 11:01.036
<i>The 5-month manhunt
began in March</i>

11:01.203 --> 11:03.955
<i>when Johnson allegedly robbed
a Loomis depository</i>

11:04.122 --> 11:07.459
<i>in Jacksonville, Florida,
before fleeing to Mexico.</i>

11:07.626 --> 11:10.295
<i>The robbery was the largest
in US history.</i>

11:10.462 --> 11:13.006
- (PHONE RINGS)
<i>- Next, your weather forecast.</i>

11:13.173 --> 11:16.176
Guess we gotta rob a bank if
we want to get on The Big Show.

11:16.343 --> 11:17.719
Yeah, I guess so.

11:17.886 --> 11:20.013
Kelly works over at Loomis.

11:20.180 --> 11:22.974
Worked. Quit three weeks ago.

11:23.141 --> 11:24.726
She's over at Hardee's now.

11:24.893 --> 11:27.104
Speaking of work,
I gotta be there in an hour.

11:27.270 --> 11:29.314
So, with that,
I'll leave you lovely people.

11:29.481 --> 11:31.358
See you, girl.

11:31.525 --> 11:33.610
(TV CHATTER CONTINUES)

11:37.197 --> 11:40.367
Hey, Kelly, seriously,
what are we talking about?

11:40.534 --> 11:42.452
- Security-wise.
- Steve, sober up. For real.

11:42.619 --> 11:44.204
I'm buzzed. I'm not drunk.

11:44.371 --> 11:45.914
Come on.
How hard can it be?

11:46.081 --> 11:48.667
You load up a truck
and you drive away.

11:48.834 --> 11:51.712
I've heard you talk about it.
Phillip Johnson did it, right?

11:51.878 --> 11:53.547
Except the getting caught part.

11:53.714 --> 11:55.257
I've known you
since we were kids.

11:55.424 --> 11:56.925
I can tell
when you're not happy.

11:57.092 --> 11:58.719
You wanna spend
the rest of your life

11:58.885 --> 12:00.721
working the Hardee's
drive-through,

12:00.887 --> 12:03.473
or do you want to be on the other side
of that drive-through

12:03.640 --> 12:05.392
pulling up
in a pink Rolls-Royce

12:05.559 --> 12:07.519
buying a year's worth
of curly fries?

12:07.686 --> 12:11.022
What I'm saying is
it's gotta be an inside job.

12:11.189 --> 12:13.817
Well, that's the thing, Steve.
I'm not inside Loomis anymore.

12:13.984 --> 12:15.527
But you must have made contacts.

12:15.694 --> 12:17.612
You flirt with every pair
of pants within five yards.

12:17.779 --> 12:18.989
No, I don't!

12:19.156 --> 12:20.699
I'm just saying
you're a people person.

12:20.866 --> 12:22.367
- That's what you're saying?
- People like you.

12:22.534 --> 12:24.578
You got that quality.

12:25.829 --> 12:28.457
I mean, there's a guy at work
that likes me, I guess.

12:28.623 --> 12:32.669
I don't flirt with him,
but my friend David.

12:32.836 --> 12:35.756
Oh. Alright, alright.

12:35.922 --> 12:37.591
That sounds promising.

12:37.758 --> 12:39.885
And just how friendly
were you and Big Dave?

12:40.051 --> 12:42.429
OK, he's practically married
and he's a good guy.

12:42.596 --> 12:44.181
Yeah. We're all good guys.

12:44.347 --> 12:47.017
I just want to know
can we trust this guy David

12:47.184 --> 12:49.019
enough just to have
a conversation?

12:49.186 --> 12:51.354
I mean, how's he feel about you?
Does he like you?

12:51.521 --> 12:53.482
Or does he "like you",
like you?

12:58.487 --> 13:00.113
(IMITATES GUNSHOT)

13:02.991 --> 13:05.076
RADIO: <i>The Congressional
Budget Office...</i>

13:05.243 --> 13:07.788
(PAGER BEEPS)

13:12.459 --> 13:15.921
- Is that your fiancée?
- No.

13:16.087 --> 13:17.881
No.

13:18.048 --> 13:19.716
You smiling like hell, man.

13:29.559 --> 13:31.895
Oh! He's here, he's here.
Right there.

13:33.730 --> 13:36.900
He's got roses.
He's got flowers.

13:37.067 --> 13:39.694
- He's perfect.
- OK, shh. Turn around.

13:39.861 --> 13:43.281
- (DOORBELL RINGS)
- (PATRONS CHATTER)

13:49.788 --> 13:52.165
I got you these at the store.

13:52.332 --> 13:55.001
Thank you. You're sweet.
They're really lovely.

13:55.168 --> 13:58.129
Well, now they have something
in common with their new owner.

13:59.297 --> 14:02.008
KELLY: Oh... Ow!

14:04.135 --> 14:05.720
There's a thorn on there.

14:05.887 --> 14:07.681
The guy at the store
said they were de-thorned.

14:07.848 --> 14:09.391
KELLY: A couple of big ones.

14:10.559 --> 14:12.853
(LAUGHS AWKWARDLY)

14:13.019 --> 14:16.690
- You look amazing, Kelly.
- Oh. Thanks. (LAUGHS)

14:16.857 --> 14:19.609
- Hair looks good.
- My friend Ricki cuts my hair.

14:19.776 --> 14:21.361
Just cut my bangs last week.

14:21.528 --> 14:23.071
Yeah, Ricki banged me out
last time.

14:23.238 --> 14:25.407
Oh.

14:26.491 --> 14:28.618
Every...

14:28.785 --> 14:31.454
You have a...

14:31.621 --> 14:33.790
- Sprung a leak in your tit.
- Oh, my gosh.

14:33.957 --> 14:36.251
Thank you.
That thorn really got me.

14:36.418 --> 14:38.795
Put some pressure on it.

14:38.962 --> 14:41.631
- DAVID: Yeah.
- (GRUNTS SOFTLY)

14:41.798 --> 14:43.842
Why isn't it milk?

14:45.051 --> 14:47.512
I think you have to have a baby
to have milk.

14:47.679 --> 14:49.472
I'm sorry.
Gosh, I'm just nervous.

14:49.639 --> 14:52.183
I'm a bigger gentleman
than that.

14:52.350 --> 14:56.646
Um, David, I wanted to explain
to you why I called you.

14:56.813 --> 14:57.981
OK.

14:58.148 --> 15:00.108
There's a gentleman
in the booth behind me...

15:00.275 --> 15:01.860
Oh, no, don't look.
Don't look.

15:02.027 --> 15:03.737
This gentleman
is a friend of mine

15:03.904 --> 15:06.907
and he has an idea
he'd like to share with you.

15:07.073 --> 15:08.992
Can he hear me right now?

15:09.159 --> 15:12.454
STEVE: I hear you.
I hear everything, David.

15:12.621 --> 15:16.833
OK. What should I call you, sir?

15:17.000 --> 15:19.961
Nothing. You don't ever need
to see me or know my name.

15:20.128 --> 15:23.882
You can refer to me as Geppetto.

15:24.049 --> 15:26.301
- Geppetto?
- STEVE: Yeah, Geppetto.

15:26.468 --> 15:30.263
As in Pinocchio.
As in I pull the strings.

15:31.348 --> 15:32.891
I think he means Stromboli.

15:33.058 --> 15:34.643
- What'd you call me?
- Nothing.

15:34.809 --> 15:36.645
I just think you mean Stromboli.

15:36.811 --> 15:38.313
Geppetto was just a wood carver.

15:38.480 --> 15:40.106
Stromboli was the puppeteer.

15:41.358 --> 15:42.734
Go ahead, though.

15:42.901 --> 15:44.986
STEVE: So Miss Campbell tells me

15:45.153 --> 15:47.238
y'all worked together
over at Loomis.

15:47.405 --> 15:49.741
Said you were one of their best
employees, a straight arrow.

15:49.908 --> 15:51.743
Clean as a nun's undies.

15:51.910 --> 15:53.662
Well, I don't know
about all that, but...

15:53.828 --> 15:55.914
STEVE: She said you're so trustworthy
you're one of

15:56.081 --> 15:58.375
the only non-managers
to have a key to the vault.

15:58.541 --> 16:00.710
I think that's
an incredible honour.

16:00.877 --> 16:04.381
I also think it's
an incredible opportunity.

16:04.547 --> 16:06.257
Do you see where I'm going
with this?

16:06.424 --> 16:09.469
Y'all aren't asking me
to go in there and take...

16:09.636 --> 16:11.763
STEVE: David,
I saw you walk in here.

16:11.930 --> 16:14.057
You're a good-looking dude.

16:14.224 --> 16:16.142
OK, there's
no getting around that.

16:16.309 --> 16:18.186
You carry your weight
in your chest

16:18.353 --> 16:20.105
and your ass and it just...

16:20.271 --> 16:23.858
You have a powerful build,
and I think you deserve more.

16:24.025 --> 16:25.694
(WHISPERS) What y'all
don't realise is...

16:25.860 --> 16:28.571
Thing is you can't pull a job off like that
on your own.

16:28.738 --> 16:30.991
You need confederates,
people with a vested interest

16:31.157 --> 16:32.826
in protecting that loot

16:32.993 --> 16:35.161
while you're laying low
down in Mejico.

16:35.328 --> 16:36.997
Loomis Fargo may look like
a big warehouse,

16:37.163 --> 16:39.290
but the money inside
belongs to the banks.

16:39.457 --> 16:42.127
If you take it, technically speaking,
you're robbing a bank.

16:42.293 --> 16:43.962
And that's a federal offence.

16:44.129 --> 16:45.922
84 months minimum.

16:46.089 --> 16:48.341
No, shh. David, just listen.

16:48.508 --> 16:51.511
We're just...
just talking, you know.

16:54.472 --> 16:56.433
STEVE: Just think about it.

16:57.475 --> 16:59.102
JANDICE: I love it, Mother.

16:59.269 --> 17:01.438
I feel like
a giant porcelain doll.

17:01.604 --> 17:03.023
Mine's a little tight,

17:03.189 --> 17:06.568
especially around the cumberbrumber...
the cucumberbun.

17:06.734 --> 17:09.237
I know it's too tight.

17:09.404 --> 17:13.116
I was hoping it would motivate you
to lose a couple pounds.

17:13.282 --> 17:15.993
Well, I stopped eating them
Goo Goo Clusters like you asked.

17:16.161 --> 17:18.246
- (LAUGHS)
- (PHONE RINGS)

17:20.832 --> 17:22.751
- Hello?
- KELLY: David?

17:24.836 --> 17:26.880
Hello? Hey.

17:27.047 --> 17:30.175
Yeah. It's a work thing.

17:36.389 --> 17:38.600
Kelly, what are you doing
calling me here?

17:38.767 --> 17:40.351
It's not a good time.

17:40.518 --> 17:43.271
Oh, OK. I was just feeling
kinda lonely.

17:43.438 --> 17:45.273
- You're lonely?
- Yeah, I mean...

17:45.440 --> 17:48.359
I don't know, I guess
I just miss you a little bit.

17:48.526 --> 17:52.155
I hope that's OK to say.
I mean, I know you're engaged.

17:52.322 --> 17:55.033
No, no, no,
don't censor yourself, please.

17:55.200 --> 17:58.536
Well, this is gonna be...
this is gonna be amazing, baby.

17:58.703 --> 18:00.538
I just don't know
if I have the nerve,

18:00.705 --> 18:02.415
you know, to take all the money

18:02.582 --> 18:05.627
and go down to Mexico
and then be on the run from the law

18:05.794 --> 18:08.088
and who knows what else
will come up out of this.

18:08.254 --> 18:10.632
The truth is
I'm a little disappointed

18:10.799 --> 18:12.383
that you don't trust me.

18:12.550 --> 18:15.553
No, Kelly, I trust you.
I just don't trust Geppetto.

18:15.720 --> 18:19.390
Well, what if, um...
what if I went with you?

18:19.557 --> 18:22.310
(GENTLE MEXICAN MUSIC)

18:22.477 --> 18:24.187
Kelly, that would be
the greatest thing

18:24.354 --> 18:27.398
that ever happened to me,
if a man's being honest.

18:27.565 --> 18:31.319
I could do that eventually.
I mean, not right at first.

18:31.486 --> 18:33.404
Oh, not at first.
No, the timing would be bad.

18:33.571 --> 18:35.281
The timing would be bad on that.

18:35.448 --> 18:37.450
You know, think about it.

18:37.617 --> 18:40.453
Two lovers on the lam in Mexico.

18:40.620 --> 18:43.957
Bonnie and Clyde. You know,
we could pop on over to Brazil.

18:44.124 --> 18:46.000
Have you ever...
ever been to Rio?

18:46.167 --> 18:47.961
I've never even been
to the airport

18:48.128 --> 18:49.712
but about twice in my life.

18:49.879 --> 18:52.048
Oh, it's a real magical place.

18:52.215 --> 18:55.343
Yeah, all those planes landing
and taking off and such.

18:55.510 --> 18:57.720
- No, Rio.
- DAVID: Oh, Rio. Yeah, yeah.

18:57.887 --> 18:59.514
You know, they say
the beaches there,

18:59.681 --> 19:01.975
they're like...
like powdered sugar.

19:02.142 --> 19:04.269
You and I can spend
all our money

19:04.435 --> 19:09.190
on fancy luxury hotels
and buy expensive negligees

19:09.357 --> 19:14.612
and just rub each other all day
with coconut...juices.

19:14.779 --> 19:16.948
Put rose petals
all over the bed.

19:17.115 --> 19:20.410
You know, just sit around
and eat jam.

19:20.577 --> 19:22.162
Hello?

19:22.328 --> 19:25.623
David, are you there?
Hello, David?

19:27.375 --> 19:29.669
Kelly, I'm in. Let's do it.

19:29.836 --> 19:31.963
Let's rob Loomis Fargo.

19:34.549 --> 19:36.092
It's gonna be amazing.

19:36.259 --> 19:38.344
OK, well, I gotta run.

19:38.511 --> 19:42.515
I gotta go
wash my pantyhose with my mouth.

19:42.682 --> 19:44.142
Do what?

19:44.309 --> 19:46.561
(SULTRY VOICE) 'Bye, David.

19:54.027 --> 19:56.321
WOMAN: There he is.

19:56.487 --> 19:58.406
The man of your dreams.

19:59.532 --> 20:01.534
He'll live here with us forever.

20:01.701 --> 20:04.120
It's like you're marrying
both of us, David.

20:04.287 --> 20:05.830
Me AND Mama.

20:05.997 --> 20:08.791
David, have you given
much thought

20:08.958 --> 20:11.127
to what you'll be doing
for your honeymoon?

20:11.294 --> 20:13.755
Yeah, I got a few plans.
Yeah, I do.

20:13.922 --> 20:15.715
I'll tell you
what he won't be doing

20:15.882 --> 20:17.884
if he doesn't lose some weight.

20:18.051 --> 20:21.179
- (BOTH LAUGH)
- (LAUGHS ZANILY)

20:21.346 --> 20:24.057
(DAVID GUFFAWS)

20:24.224 --> 20:27.936
(WHEEZES
AND CONTINUES LAUGHING)

20:30.605 --> 20:33.316
That's a good Goo Goo Cluster.

20:36.319 --> 20:38.446
(SLAMS DOOR)

20:38.613 --> 20:41.199
(ROCK MUSIC)

20:45.203 --> 20:47.580
SONG: ♪ Bang goes the gun

20:47.747 --> 20:50.750
♪ But I'm already gone

20:52.001 --> 20:54.921
♪ Bang goes the gun

20:55.088 --> 20:58.007
♪ But I'm already gone

20:58.174 --> 21:00.009
♪ I'm a lean machine

21:00.176 --> 21:01.844
♪ I'm ready and mean

21:02.011 --> 21:04.514
♪ I'm always on the run

21:05.640 --> 21:08.393
♪ Bang goes the gun

21:08.559 --> 21:12.772
♪ I'm already gone... ♪

21:12.939 --> 21:14.649
Where's the money?
Who else is involved?

21:14.816 --> 21:17.360
- We know you have the money!
- (SNEEZES)

21:17.527 --> 21:19.570
- Come on!
- (GRUNTS)

21:19.737 --> 21:21.281
KELLY: Oh. Oh.

21:21.447 --> 21:23.199
- (GRUNTS)
- Close. Close.

21:23.366 --> 21:25.076
Come on, pick up the pace!

21:25.243 --> 21:28.162
In Mexico, you may have to
live off the land for a little bit.

21:28.329 --> 21:30.581
- Yeah.
- I got you a tarantula.

21:30.748 --> 21:32.125
- DAVID: Whoa!
- He's dead.

21:32.292 --> 21:33.668
- Don't worry.
- He's dead?

21:33.835 --> 21:37.380
Maybe you should try him.
Get your immune system built up.

21:49.767 --> 21:51.769
- (KELLY GROANS)
- That's not bad.

21:51.936 --> 21:53.896
That's not as bad
as I thought it'd be.

21:58.401 --> 22:01.446
(GROANS) What the hell you doing
in my house?!

22:01.612 --> 22:03.323
- Sorry! Sorry!
- Who do you think you are?!

22:03.489 --> 22:04.949
My apologies, sir!

22:05.116 --> 22:06.743
- (MAN SHOUTS)
- Kelly!

22:12.832 --> 22:15.668
♪ Bang goes the gun

22:15.835 --> 22:19.881
♪ But I'm already gone

22:20.048 --> 22:22.425
♪ Bang goes the gun

22:22.592 --> 22:26.262
♪ But I'm already gone

22:26.429 --> 22:29.390
♪ Bang goes the gun

22:29.557 --> 22:32.977
♪ I'm already gone

22:33.144 --> 22:36.147
♪ Aah! ♪

22:38.149 --> 22:40.068
Are you sure McKinney's OK

22:40.234 --> 22:41.944
with me jacking with
his identification?

22:42.111 --> 22:44.238
Yes, yes, McKinney doesn't
value government documents

22:44.405 --> 22:45.907
the way you and me do.

22:46.074 --> 22:47.450
- It's...
- (MAN CHATTERS)

22:47.617 --> 22:48.701
There's Ghantt.

22:48.868 --> 22:50.745
GHANTT'S PARTNER: Ghantt, man!

22:53.331 --> 22:56.376
- DAVID: Have a good weekend.
- Hey, look, you too, man.

23:00.004 --> 23:01.756
DAVID: Tell your kids
I said hello.

23:01.923 --> 23:03.424
GHANTT'S PARTNER:
Yeah, OK. You too.

23:08.054 --> 23:10.681
(CAR ENGINE TURNS
BUT DOESN'T START)

23:15.812 --> 23:19.649
(TENSE MUSIC)

23:30.076 --> 23:32.703
Come on, David, you got this.

23:33.955 --> 23:35.415
It's go time.

23:42.046 --> 23:44.382
(SCANNER BLIPS, LOCK BUZZES)

23:54.434 --> 23:56.519
(TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES)

23:57.562 --> 23:58.980
(SCANNER BLIPS)

24:19.876 --> 24:22.503
(EPIC ROCK MUSIC)

24:45.485 --> 24:47.028
(MUSIC ENDS)

24:54.410 --> 24:56.579
(FRENETIC ROCK MUSIC)

25:08.466 --> 25:09.967
(GRUNTS)

25:17.934 --> 25:19.936
David, are you there?

25:21.395 --> 25:23.731
Kelly, guess what I'm doing
right now.

25:23.898 --> 25:26.901
- What? What are you doing?
- I'm robbing a Loomis Fargo!

25:27.068 --> 25:29.237
I knew you could do it.
I'm so proud of you.

25:29.403 --> 25:31.739
It's just paper. It's a lot of paper,
but it's just paper.

25:31.906 --> 25:33.824
Yeah, paper that's gonna
change our life.

25:33.991 --> 25:36.077
"Our life." I like that.

25:36.244 --> 25:39.038
Two lives, one heart,
like conjoined twins, right?

25:39.205 --> 25:40.831
Hey, enough with the love-fest.

25:40.998 --> 25:42.792
I need you to come back
from Planet Cornball

25:42.959 --> 25:44.627
and focus on the robbery.

25:44.794 --> 25:47.421
Geppetto, this happens to be
a private conversation, OK?

25:47.588 --> 25:49.465
No! This is NOT
a private conversation.

25:49.632 --> 25:52.677
It's a robbery. Now, I bought
these walkie-talkies...

25:52.843 --> 25:53.928
(STATIC CRACKLES)

26:00.893 --> 26:02.562
Ghantt, you got a bogie
flying in.

26:02.728 --> 26:04.480
Repeat, you've got company.

26:04.647 --> 26:06.440
David, it's Ty, it's Ty.
He's coming's back!

26:06.607 --> 26:08.109
Ghantt, do you copy?
You've got...

26:08.276 --> 26:10.111
(STATIC CRACKLES)

26:11.779 --> 26:14.073
(SCANNER BLIPS, LOCK BUZZES)

26:17.535 --> 26:20.246
(TIMECARD PUNCHER CLANGS)

26:24.083 --> 26:25.251
(CONTAINER SCRAPES LOUDLY)

26:27.503 --> 26:29.380
(UNEASY MUSIC)

26:33.926 --> 26:37.972
TY: Hey. Who's that?

26:43.936 --> 26:45.563
What the hell is going on here?

26:45.730 --> 26:49.191
I'm gonna tell Chad on your ass.
I caught you red-handed.

26:49.358 --> 26:52.194
Ty, listen here. This ain't
what you think, buddy.

26:52.361 --> 26:54.530
Screw Ty. Just don't cut Ty in.

26:54.697 --> 26:56.657
(STAMMERS)

26:59.785 --> 27:01.829
You said there wasn't
no overtime this weekend.

27:02.872 --> 27:05.750
No, you're...you're right.
There's no overtime.

27:05.916 --> 27:08.794
It's just... I'm just picking up
an extra shift.

27:08.961 --> 27:12.298
- The next one is mine.
- The next one's yours, yeah.

27:12.465 --> 27:14.550
Sneaky ass.

27:15.926 --> 27:17.511
Say hi to your kids, alright?

27:17.678 --> 27:19.430
(SCANNER BLIPS, LOCK BUZZES)

27:26.187 --> 27:27.730
(STATIC CRACKLES)

27:29.106 --> 27:31.484
STEVE: I repeat, Ghantt,
do you need backup?

27:31.651 --> 27:33.736
What is your situation in there?
Do you need...

27:33.903 --> 27:36.739
Yeah, I... I...
That's my fault, Geppetto.

27:36.906 --> 27:38.616
I turned it off by accident, OK?

27:38.783 --> 27:40.868
David, stay calm.
You got this.

27:41.035 --> 27:43.788
- Yeah, OK, yeah.
- Just listen to me.

27:43.954 --> 27:46.957
(SINGS WORDLESSLY
IN SULTRY VOICE)

27:47.124 --> 27:50.378
(KELLY'S VOICE ECHOES
TUNEFULLY)

27:50.544 --> 27:51.879
(SINGS LOW NOTES)

27:52.046 --> 27:53.422
♪ No, no, no, no

27:53.589 --> 27:55.508
(RAPIDLY CHANGES NOTE)

27:55.675 --> 27:57.093
(KELLY'S VOICE ECHOES
TUNEFULLY)

27:57.259 --> 27:59.345
Kelly, I could listen to that
all day.

27:59.512 --> 28:01.222
But let me get
my robbery going, OK?

28:01.389 --> 28:02.556
♪ Ooh, oooh... ♪

28:02.723 --> 28:04.767
(EPIC ROCK MUSIC)

28:09.480 --> 28:11.399
STEVE: Ghantt,
it's been two hours.

28:11.565 --> 28:14.193
What is taking you so long?!
Over.

28:15.820 --> 28:18.114
OK, I think that's everything
but the cameras.

28:20.741 --> 28:23.536
You fucking maggot pig!

28:23.703 --> 28:27.248
(EPIC ROCK MUSIC CONTINUES)

28:51.897 --> 28:53.858
Whoo!

29:00.281 --> 29:01.824
(MUSIC FADES)

29:17.548 --> 29:19.425
(DOOR LOCKS)

29:19.592 --> 29:22.219
No! No!

29:26.182 --> 29:28.184
I'm locked in!

29:28.350 --> 29:30.936
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC)

29:51.415 --> 29:54.543
(SIGHS) These birthing hips.

30:19.777 --> 30:21.654
(ENGINE STARTS)

30:23.447 --> 30:25.616
(EPIC ROCK MUSIC CONTINUES)

30:26.867 --> 30:29.411
(TYRES SCREECH)

30:31.997 --> 30:34.083
DAVID: Aaaaaaaargh!

30:35.501 --> 30:37.545
- Nuggets!
- STEVE: Whoa!

30:37.711 --> 30:40.464
Oh, God, my nuggets
are bruising!

30:40.631 --> 30:44.969
- What's he doing?!
- (SHOUTS) Help!

30:45.135 --> 30:48.472
(DRAMATIC MUSIC)

30:54.019 --> 30:55.187
Help!

30:56.355 --> 30:58.190
STEVE: Don't let him
see your face.

30:58.357 --> 31:00.401
Ghantt, you idiot!
What are you doing?!

31:00.568 --> 31:03.028
- Unlock the door.
- I'm stuck!

31:03.195 --> 31:04.697
STEVE: Check that door
over there.

31:04.864 --> 31:06.782
You idiot, you drove it
right into the ditch!

31:06.949 --> 31:09.952
- This door's locked too.
- He said this one's locked too.

31:10.119 --> 31:11.495
Sonofa...

31:11.662 --> 31:14.331
Any of you yard apes
try the back?

31:14.498 --> 31:16.500
- Did you try it?
- No.

31:17.543 --> 31:20.129
(MUSIC BUILDS)

31:34.727 --> 31:36.979
I'm sorry this isn't
too comfortable for you.

31:37.146 --> 31:38.772
No, it's OK.

31:38.939 --> 31:41.525
It should get you through the airport.
It's about 20 grand.

31:41.692 --> 31:44.028
I'm gonna start you off light
and send you the rest.

31:44.194 --> 31:46.030
Well, 20 grand's good
where I come from.

31:46.196 --> 31:47.990
- That's a year's salary.
- (LAUGHS)

31:48.157 --> 31:51.327
Yeah, it is, isn't it? Yeah.

31:51.493 --> 31:53.203
We did it.

31:53.370 --> 31:55.831
Well, YOU did it.

31:57.082 --> 31:59.335
Oh, here. Geppetto wanted me
to give you this.

31:59.501 --> 32:01.670
It's your fake ID.

32:01.837 --> 32:04.632
DAVID: So my name's
Michael McKinney now?

32:04.798 --> 32:06.425
McKinney, yeah.
He's actually a real person.

32:06.592 --> 32:08.052
He's friends with Geppetto.
Oh, here.

32:08.218 --> 32:09.803
He gave us his birth certificate

32:09.970 --> 32:12.056
to give to you too,
so take that.

32:13.098 --> 32:15.351
Oh, here, this is a disguise
I made for you

32:15.517 --> 32:19.146
for leaving the country
or whatever.

32:20.522 --> 32:23.108
(INDISTINCT P.A. ANNOUNCEMENT)

32:23.275 --> 32:25.444
KELLY: OK, you ready to go?

32:26.987 --> 32:28.864
Oh... Oh.

32:29.031 --> 32:31.992
Gosh, yeah, I'm sorry
about those contacts again.

32:32.159 --> 32:34.203
I thought 'anaconda'
was a brand name.

32:34.370 --> 32:36.747
No, I like it.
This is a top-shelf disguise.

32:36.914 --> 32:40.334
I look like if Jesus and a cat
had a baby.

32:40.501 --> 32:42.711
- (CHUCKLES) Yeah, you do, kinda.
- Yeah.

32:42.878 --> 32:44.630
Which is a nice thought too,
you know?

32:44.797 --> 32:47.800
- It is. Well, he made cats, so...
