55:27.074 --> 55:28.743
- No, not to the right!
- (TYRES SCREECH)

55:28.909 --> 55:30.494
(PEOPLE SCREAM)

55:30.661 --> 55:32.747
(COMMOTION)

55:39.253 --> 55:40.796
(BUZZES)

55:46.260 --> 55:48.429
(SIGHS)

55:48.596 --> 55:50.431
- (PHONE RINGS)
- David?

55:50.598 --> 55:51.974
I thought
I'd never hear your voice.

55:52.141 --> 55:53.392
- I was...
- Are you OK?

55:53.559 --> 55:55.728
Well, I mean, a man is trying
to murder me here.

55:55.895 --> 55:57.438
They chased me
all the way around town.

55:57.605 --> 55:59.940
A big old pervert-looking guy.
I think he's trying to kill me.

56:00.107 --> 56:01.776
I don't know
if he's done with me,

56:01.942 --> 56:03.402
but I don't know
what's going on.

56:03.569 --> 56:06.364
David, look, I'm sorry.
Steve just...he panicked.

56:06.530 --> 56:09.283
You weren't ever supposed
to know his real name.

56:09.450 --> 56:11.410
And I just...
I tried to send you a message.

56:11.577 --> 56:13.371
I tried to warn you
he'd do something.

56:13.537 --> 56:15.373
Steve said he was gonna
try to kill me?

56:15.539 --> 56:17.708
Why would he, if he knew
you and me was lovers?

56:17.875 --> 56:19.585
That don't make any sense!

56:19.752 --> 56:22.671
OK, well...the truth is...

56:24.799 --> 56:27.343
..I don't believe Steve was ever
gonna send you any money.

56:27.510 --> 56:29.553
And he's been playing you
the whole time.

56:29.720 --> 56:32.723
And I swear I never knew
his intentions, I swear.

56:32.890 --> 56:34.850
David?

56:35.017 --> 56:37.645
What were your intentions,
Kelly?

56:38.896 --> 56:40.439
Um...

56:41.941 --> 56:43.651
I don't know.

56:43.818 --> 56:46.570
I guess I just figured
you'd go down to Mexico

56:46.737 --> 56:49.448
and order a round of daiquiris
with flowers in them

56:49.615 --> 56:52.868
and meet a little mamacita
and forget all about me.

56:53.035 --> 56:55.704
But...you didn't.

56:55.871 --> 56:57.623
No, no, Kelly, you was gonna be
my mamacita.

56:57.790 --> 56:59.333
I don't know what to say...

56:59.500 --> 57:01.085
David, you are
such a wonderful person.

57:01.252 --> 57:02.878
You have to know
that I think that.

57:03.045 --> 57:05.256
Just shut up, Kelly!
Just shut up!

57:06.674 --> 57:08.384
David...

57:08.551 --> 57:11.846
You always told me to stand up
for myself. Well, here goes.

57:12.012 --> 57:16.559
You are a manipulator
of human emotions.

57:16.725 --> 57:21.063
And I never, ever want to talk
to you again.

57:21.230 --> 57:23.107
Wait, Dav...

57:27.153 --> 57:30.739
(SAD MUSIC)

57:30.906 --> 57:34.034
(WOMEN SPEAK SPANISH)

57:36.871 --> 57:38.539
(BURPS)

57:41.792 --> 57:43.627
(CRIES)

57:50.885 --> 57:52.470
(CLANG!)

57:55.306 --> 57:57.391
(SINISTER MUSIC)

57:57.558 --> 57:59.393
(MIKE GRUNTS)

57:59.560 --> 58:02.771
- (THUD!)
- (EXHALES) There we go.

58:04.565 --> 58:07.234
Oh. Look who's awake.

58:07.401 --> 58:10.154
Hey, whoa, whoa.
What's going on here?

58:10.321 --> 58:12.490
- I'm accessing the sewer line.
- (PIPE CLANKS)

58:13.616 --> 58:15.659
What's going down there?

58:15.826 --> 58:18.287
You mean down here?

58:19.580 --> 58:20.956
That's gonna be you.

58:21.123 --> 58:24.168
You listen to me.
I-I-I can pay you.

58:24.335 --> 58:26.587
- I can pay you.
- Oh, yeah? What do you got?

58:26.754 --> 58:28.547
Give me that.

58:30.424 --> 58:32.343
(CHUCKLES)

58:33.594 --> 58:35.846
Let's see what kind of scratch
we're talking about.

58:36.013 --> 58:38.599
5, 20, another 20...

58:38.766 --> 58:40.434
I'll get you more. OK?

58:40.601 --> 58:42.520
- $48.
- I-I got... I can get you more.

58:42.686 --> 58:45.189
I don't know if this is
going to be enough. You know.

58:48.192 --> 58:52.780
Yeah. That's too bad.
I was open to negotiation.

58:54.031 --> 58:56.700
But at this point, I reckon
I'm just gonna have to do it

58:56.867 --> 58:58.410
the way I'd already
dreamt about it.

58:58.577 --> 59:01.330
Hey, uh, listen here.
You listen here.

59:01.497 --> 59:04.333
Wait. Hey, hey, hey. Easy.

59:07.086 --> 59:08.796
Where do you think
you're going, huh?

59:08.963 --> 59:11.131
Anywhere you're going from now,
I'm gonna send you, OK?

59:11.298 --> 59:12.466
(WHIMPERS)

59:12.633 --> 59:14.051
You ain't got nothing
to worry about

59:14.218 --> 59:16.428
travel-wise now, mister, uh...

59:19.056 --> 59:20.849
..Michael McKinney.

59:24.478 --> 59:26.188
Your name's Michael McKinney?

59:27.314 --> 59:28.857
Yeah.

59:30.359 --> 59:32.361
Michael Aaron McKinney?

59:35.739 --> 59:36.824
Yeah.

59:38.367 --> 59:40.160
Dang.

59:40.327 --> 59:42.288
They never told me.

59:42.454 --> 59:44.915
That's my name too.

59:49.003 --> 59:50.546
(KNIFE CLANKS)

59:53.382 --> 59:56.010
What...? Where'd...?

59:56.176 --> 59:59.179
You were born
on May 8, 1961, huh?

59:59.346 --> 01:00:03.642
- Uh, not... Yeah.
- In, uh, St Francis Hospital?

01:00:03.809 --> 01:00:05.561
Pigeon Forge, Tennessee?
Is that right?

01:00:05.728 --> 01:00:08.314
Yeah. Uh, home of Dollywood.

01:00:16.989 --> 01:00:20.951
Your name
is Michael Aaron McKinney.

01:00:21.118 --> 01:00:22.995
Yeah.

01:00:24.371 --> 01:00:28.125
Me name Michael Aaron McKinney.

01:00:28.292 --> 01:00:30.544
I don't know what that means,

01:00:30.711 --> 01:00:35.049
but what I do know is that God
or the galaxy

01:00:35.215 --> 01:00:37.468
has brought us together.

01:00:37.635 --> 01:00:39.470
Yeah.

01:00:41.722 --> 01:00:43.557
This means you ain't gonna
cut me up, right?

01:00:43.724 --> 01:00:46.852
(CRIES)

01:00:51.273 --> 01:00:53.609
Forgive me, Michael.

01:00:54.985 --> 01:00:57.363
You gotta forgive me, please.

01:00:57.529 --> 01:00:58.739
Oh, I do.

01:00:58.906 --> 01:01:01.075
I forgive you.

01:01:02.201 --> 01:01:04.370
Just like that.

01:01:04.536 --> 01:01:07.247
(SOBS) Please.

01:01:07.414 --> 01:01:10.000
(SEAGULLS CRY)

01:01:11.627 --> 01:01:14.338
Hey, you ever see
'The Parent Trap'?

01:01:14.505 --> 01:01:18.509
That Walt Disney film with
that...that Hayley Mills lady?

01:01:18.676 --> 01:01:20.761
That was a powerful flick.
I remember that movie.

01:01:20.928 --> 01:01:23.639
About how them two girls,
they raised separately,

01:01:23.806 --> 01:01:25.766
but then they meet each other
at summer camp

01:01:25.933 --> 01:01:27.351
and it blows
their tiny minds.

01:01:27.518 --> 01:01:29.478
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

01:01:29.645 --> 01:01:31.980
That's kind of
how I feel right now.

01:01:32.147 --> 01:01:35.275
- Yeah. Yeah.
- You know what I'm wondering?

01:01:35.442 --> 01:01:37.903
Seeing as we was born in the
same hospital on the same day...

01:01:38.070 --> 01:01:39.488
Yeah.

01:01:39.655 --> 01:01:41.365
..we must have been
right next to each other

01:01:41.532 --> 01:01:42.616
in that little
baby place, right?

01:01:42.783 --> 01:01:44.702
That makes sense, yeah.

01:01:44.868 --> 01:01:47.162
Well, maybe at some point,
I turned and looked at you

01:01:47.329 --> 01:01:51.083
and you rolled over,
you...staring at me,

01:01:51.250 --> 01:01:53.794
and even though our eyes
was all gooey and whatnot,

01:01:53.961 --> 01:01:56.463
we made a promise to one another
right then and there

01:01:56.630 --> 01:01:59.425
that we'd find each other again
some day.

01:01:59.591 --> 01:02:01.510
Yeah, yeah. I reckon we did.

01:02:01.677 --> 01:02:03.846
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

01:02:04.930 --> 01:02:07.933
I like you, Michael McKinney.
And I'm awful glad we met.

01:02:08.100 --> 01:02:12.521
Yeah. I'm glad we met too.
Been a pretty good hang.

01:02:12.688 --> 01:02:15.315
(LAID-BACK MUSIC)

01:02:40.257 --> 01:02:42.259
Sleep tight, little brother.

01:02:51.852 --> 01:02:53.395
(DOOR CLOSES)

01:02:58.025 --> 01:02:59.568
(SIGHS)

01:03:01.570 --> 01:03:04.656
Miss Campbell, how long
did you know David Ghantt?

01:03:04.823 --> 01:03:09.953
Um... I don't know. Around four months,
I guess. M-maybe five.

01:03:10.120 --> 01:03:13.040
And during the time that
you were partnered with him,

01:03:13.207 --> 01:03:14.958
did he seem restless?

01:03:15.125 --> 01:03:18.629
No. Not that I remember. No.

01:03:18.796 --> 01:03:22.090
I mean, I...I don't really
know him too well. So...

01:03:22.257 --> 01:03:25.636
- Huh. Miss Campbell...
- Look. Um...

01:03:25.803 --> 01:03:28.305
I know you're just two good men
doing a difficult job,

01:03:28.472 --> 01:03:31.850
but, uh, I only worked there
for a short while, and...

01:03:32.017 --> 01:03:34.728
You know, maybe you should talk
to someone who worked at Loomis

01:03:34.895 --> 01:03:41.068
at the time that David Ghantt
committed his atrocities.

01:03:41.235 --> 01:03:44.446
Well, that's what we did.
And you know what they told us?

01:03:44.613 --> 01:03:47.407
They said, "Talk to Kelly Campbell.
